(ooc: meanie!)

Element saw one of his missiles hit Firearm. He hadn't meant to do it, but 
he felt bad about it anyways. Menasor was going to pay for this. Element 
sped up after Menasor, quickly gaining on him. He fired four more missiles 
at him, one from every missile launcher, but this time he mentally guided 
them toward Menasor's back and well away from Firearm.

In Element's mind, the portion of him that was Mantle was pushing forward to 
get Firearm back. He wasn't going to let Menasor escape. Mantle was a bot 
who valued his friends, and he considered Firearm a friend now that he had 
felt his mind. Element tried to tackle Menasor as he got close, speeding up 
as he did so.
